flowRoot.flowPara: If one or multiple players wish to challenge the current witchfinder general they can ask for another vote.
Players can then nominate them selves to run for witch finder general.
All players can then vote on their prefered candidate with a show of hands.
A player can abstain from voting if they wish.
The player with the most votes takes the WFG card and is the new witchfinder general.
If the vote is a tie then a coin flip can be used to determine the winner.
Before executing one of the players the Witchfinder General may choose to interrogate people to determine who they are.
Example questions may be:
- Are you a Witch/Cultist?
- Have you ever communed with Satan?
- How much do you like being poked with a pin?
- Are you a Witch/Cultist? (but this time shouting)
The witchfinder general may execute one person at a time.
The Player to be executed must be alive and not have been the Witchhunter General on the previous round.
The executed person is given a ghost card and is then dead.
If you are executed:
- Do Not reveal your role card
- You may look at one other
players card.
- You may no longer vote
Once a player has been executed other players may then challenge the current WFG. In that case see the voting instructions.
The game ends if either all the cultists or all the witches are executed.
If all the cultsits die then they must reveal their cards.
If all the Witches Die they must reveal their cards
only one election
If a witch is elected the witches and cultists win.
If a Witchfinder is elected the witchfinders win.
